	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" /><div class="quotetitle">tokumaru wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><div class="quotetitle">kyuusaku wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">it would need to nondestructively interrupt the game</div><br />I don't know... executing extra code while the games run (to check for the specific button sequence) might break them, even if if it's just a little bit of code... So I don't think this is such a good idea.</div>
<br />No extra code would be run until the game is halted, button checking can be done in hardware by adding a serial load shift register decoded to the controller ports. The outputs would be XNORed with a programmable button register then those outputs could be ANDed to trigger a match.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


